      "source": [
        "## Download Images From Open Images Dataset V7\n",
        "Open Images Dataset V7 is a large-scale dataset of annotated images The Open Images Dataset V7 contains over 14 million images, each of which is labeled with one or more objects or scenes.\n",
        "\n",
        "We used OIDv4_ToolKit to download the images. In our case, we initially chose three classes:\n",
        "\n",
        "*   Hand gun\n",
        "*   Knife\n",
        "*   Mobile phone\n",
        "\n",
        "\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "FpBJGUJfpsnK"
      }
    },

        "## Install YOLOv8\n",
        "\n",
        "YOLOv8 is a real-time object detection algorithm that is an extension of the YOLO (You Only Look Once) family of models. It is a deep learning-based method that uses a single neural network to predict bounding boxes and class probabilities directly from full images, without the need for region proposal networks (RPNs) or other post-processing steps."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "2YQC6__X_eVu"
      }
    },
